OL,3,CFormer UK Border chief says ETA
OL,4,Cloophole poses 'risk' for authorities
OL,6,FThey do have to show a valid French ID
OL,7,Fcard and travel on an approved ferry
OL,8,Fservice but would then be within the
OL,9,FCommon Travel Area - with no hard
OL,10,Fborder between the Channel Islands and
OL,11,Fthe UK.
OL,13,FAlthough airlines and ferry operators
OL,14,Foften perform ID checks on passengers,
OL,15,FMr Smith says the role of Jersey and
OL,16,FGuernsey's border authorities is key
OL,17,Fto ensuring the route is not exploited.
OL,19,FHe explains: "There is a bigger risk
OL,20,Fof identity cards being abused than
OL,21,Fpassports.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/7
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
